				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's a bad idea to assume the sizes of the integral types in C and C++. It's much better to use unsigned int with bit masks. For example:
<br />
<br />(unsigned char) x -&gt; x &amp; 0xFF
<br />~x -&gt; x ^ 0xFF or x ^ 0xFFFF
<br />x + y &lt; x -&gt; ((x + y) &amp; 0xFF) &lt; x
<br />
<br />If you feel you must use integral types instead of masks, use uint8_t and uint16_t, accessible with #include &lt;stdint.h&gt;.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

